notesStmt.note: Incipit: Cum praecognitionis nominis logicae et huius obiecti coniungas originem, divisionem, finem, utilitatem supponentes (f. 2r).

supportDesc.extent: 337 leaves, ill. : 205 x 156 (162 x 106) mm. bound to 209 x 157 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 337; 1-38, 45-90, 100-115, 117-199, 201-322, 324-339, 343-356, 358-359, [i], contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto; [1-337]; modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto. There appear to be gaps in numbering between f. 90 and 100, 115 and 117, and 199 and 201 rather than leaves lacking. Folios 39-44, 322-323, 340-342, and 356-357 appear to be lacking. Final leaf is not bound in. References in this record are to the modern foliation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with secular material in Latin and Italian in another hand (f. 336r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Decorated title page with monogram of Jesus Christ (f. 1r); decorated initials throughout, some with faces (for example, f. 14r); decorated headings, captions, and tailpieces throughout; diagram of Aristotle's square of opposition (f. 27r); diagram of Porphyrian tree (titled Arbor Porphyriana) bearing the inscription: V V. Braydense Collegium Mediolanse et Soc. Jesu (f. 336r).
Decorated initial, Initial C, Face, f. 14r
